<!-- Page Content -->
<div class="rules-container">
    <div class="rules-header">Cemetery Rules & Regulations</div>

    <div class="rules-section">
        <h3>Ownership and Authority</h3>
        <p>The Paradise Avenue Muslim Cemetery is the sole property of the <strong>Connecticut Council of Masajid (CCM)</strong>. The CCM reserves the right to allow or deny burials at its discretion without liability.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="rules-section">
        <h3>Eligibility</h3>
        <p>Only Muslims whose faith conforms to the Quran and Sunnah may be buried here. All grave structures must be approved by CCM. For complete guidelines, contact the CCM Administrative Office at <strong>(203) 562-2757</strong>.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="rules-section">
        <h3>General Regulations</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Burial request must be submitted via online registration form or in person with proper documentation.</li>
            <li>Minimum 24-hour notice is required before burial for digging arrangements.</li>
            <li>Burials must occur during daylight hours only; no lighting is available at the site.</li>
            <li>No reservation of plots; burials proceed in sequence.</li>
            <li>No raised graves, cement, bricks, tombs, mausoleums, or fences allowed.</li>
            <li>No headstones or markers may be installed unless CCM authorized.</li>
            <li>No alterations or decorations are permitted without written approval.</li>
            <li>Vehicles must remain in the parking lot; only maintenance vehicles are permitted inside the cemetery.</li>
            <li>No flowers in containers, pots, baskets, or vases.</li>
            <li>No plant-picking or damage to trees, shrubs, or cemetery structures.</li>
            <li>Profane language or disorderly conduct is prohibited on cemetery grounds.</li>
            <li>No signs, advertisements, or unauthorized postings are allowed.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="rules-section">
        <h3>Responsibilities</h3>
        <p>CCM maintains the entire cemetery but welcomes donations and volunteer support from families and community members. Donations should be mailed to the CCM address listed on our website.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="rules-section">
        <h3>Winter Burials</h3>
        <p>If winter weather prevents a burial, the deceased may remain at the funeral home until burial becomes possible.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="rules-section">
        <h3>Online Registration Acknowledgement</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>I affirm the deceased was a practicing Muslim who believed in Allah and Muhammad (PBUH).</li>
            <li>I understand CCM provides land, digging, and maintenance only. Funeral arrangements are my responsibility.</li>
            <li>All burial charges must be paid online or to the Operations Manager before burial begins.</li>
            <li>I agree to indemnify and hold harmless CCM from liability related to burial arrangements.</li>
            <li>I understand CCM prohibits exhumation of any buried person.</li>
            <li>I have read and agree to comply with all CCM rules and regulations.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="note-box">
        <strong>Note:</strong> The CCM may amend, repeal, or introduce new rules at any time without prior notice. All visitors are requested to help preserve the dignity and sanctity of the cemetery grounds.
    </div>
</div>
